                            <comment id="412566" author="JIRAUSER18900" created="Thu, 25 Apr 2024 16:21:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I get you.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Suggested resolution is to rewrite section 33.2 in the docs, then? I&apos;d be happy with that as a resolution.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="412535" author="adilger" created="Thu, 25 Apr 2024 14:13:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We haven&apos;t been using sgpdd for testing in a while, I think that fio is being used on the storage devices. Since this is destructive to the device data, even that is not run very frequently. &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="412531" author="JIRAUSER18900" created="Thu, 25 Apr 2024 13:45:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Haven&apos;t done sgpdd-survey in a few months, but the troublesome lines are still there in 2.15.4 / master so I&apos;m certainly anticipating the issue remains.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Current Lustre docs don&apos;t point to using raw devices for testing, at least, but the man pages for sgp_dd do, so it&apos;s a toss up whether the wrapper script should handle this, or some note added in the docs to not have other people fall into the trap.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="412514" author="pjones" created="Thu, 25 Apr 2024 11:54:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Gwen&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Is this issue still a concern for you?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
